headlines.description: Premier League leaders Arsenal dropped points at home for the first time this season as they were held to a goalless draw by Newcastle United.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leaders Arsenal frustrated in draw with Newcastle

headlines.description: Everton were thrashed 4-1 at home by Brighton & Hove Albion, who scored three goals in five second-half minutes at Goodison Park.
headlines.shortLinkText: Everton thrashed 4-1 at home by Brighton

headlines.description: Fulham's Aleksandar Mitrovic continued his fine season in front of goal after his first-half strike earned them a 1-0 win at Leicester on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitrovic sends Fulham past Leciester into seventh place

headlines.description: Manchester United beat AFC Bournemouth 3-0 on Tuesday night at Old Trafford to draw level with Newcastle on points in the Premier League table.
headlines.shortLinkText: Man United beat Bournemouth to solidify top-4
